"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10201","id":"10201","name":"AWS Compatibility"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/11504","id":"11504","name":"EC2"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/13601","id":"13601","name":"VPC"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"customfield_13000":null,"description":"Per http://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/reference/ec2/create-route.html, when specifying an instance ID as target of a route, \"The operation fails if you specify an instance ID unless exactly one network interface is attached.\"\r\n\r\nAlthough the behavior is correct (i.e., adding a route using an instance with multiple ENIs fails), the error message is misleading:\r\n\r\n{noformat}\r\n# euca-create-route -r 255.0.0.1/32 -i i-554b10f2 rtb-ec8e0ebf\r\neuca-create-route: error (InvalidInstanceID): Network interface not found for i-554b10f2\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nThe message is at least incomplete: a network interface to be used as route target was not found (given that the instance has multiple interfaces). Ideally, the message should convey that instances with multiple ENIs cannot be used as route target.\r\n\r\nAWS error message:\r\n{noformat}\r\n# euca-create-route -r 255.0.0.1/32 -i i-0ddc07f0fc89b8af6 rtb-e88e2b8d --region euca@us-east-1\r\neuca-create-route: error (InvalidInstanceID): There are multiple interfaces attached to instance 'i-0ddc07f0fc89b8af6'. Please specify an interface ID for the operation instead.\r\n{noformat}","customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"aggregatetimeestimate":null,"attachment":[],"summary":"Misleading error message when trying to add a route targeting an instance with multiple ENIs","creator":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=tsugawa","name":"tsugawa","key":"tsugawa","accountId":"557058